<doc>
  <member name="IMFPMPClient.SetPMPHost">
    <summary>
      <para>Provides a pointer to the <see cref="IMFPMPHost" /> interface.</para>
    </summary>
    <param name="pPMPHost">
      <para>A pointer to the <see cref="IMFPMPHost" /> interface.</para>
    </param>
    <returns>
      <para>If this method succeeds, it returns <b>S_OK</b>. Otherwise, it returns an <b>HRESULT</b> error code.</para>
    </returns>
    <remarks>
      <para>The <see cref="IMFPMPHost" /> pointer is apartment threaded. The media source must add the pointer to the global interface table (GIT) before using it.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso cref="IMFPMPClient" />
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/medfound/pmp-media-session">PMP Media Session</seealso>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/medfound/protected-media-path">Protected Media Path</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="IMFPMPClient">
    <summary>
      <para>Enables a media source to receive a pointer to the <see cref="IMFPMPHost" /> interface.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>If a media source exposes this interface, the Protected Media Path (PMP) Media Session calls <see cref="SetPMPHost" /> with a pointer to the <see cref="IMFPMPHost" /> interface. The media source can use the <b>IMFPMPHost</b> interface to create objects in the PMP process.</para>
    </remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/medfound/media-foundation-interfaces">Media Foundation Interfaces</seealso>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/medfound/pmp-media-session">PMP Media Session</seealso>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/medfound/protected-media-path">Protected Media Path</seealso>
  </member>
</doc>